thy C.|year=1979|title=Self and Society in Tang Dynasty Love Tales|journal=Journal of the American Oriental Society |volume=99|issue=1|pages=95\u2013100|jstor=598956}}\n* {{citation |last=Wright|first=Arthur F.|title=Buddhism in Chinese History|year=1959|publisher=Stanford University Press|location=Stanford}}\n* {{Citation |doi=10.1086/352793|last=Xi|first=Zezong|year=1981|title=Chinese Studies in the History of Astronomy, 1949\u20131979|journal=Isis|volume=72|issue=3|pages=456\u2013470|bibcode=1981Isis...72..456X}}\n* {{citation |last=Xu|first=Daoxun|others=et al.|title=The Biography of Tang Xuanzong|year=1993|newspaper=People's Press|location=Beijing|isbn=978-7-01-001210-0}}\n* {{citation |last=Xue|first=Zongzheng|authorlink=Xue Zongzheng|title=Turkic peoples (\u7a81\u53a5\u53f2)|year=1992|publisher=\u4e2d\u56fd\u793e\u4f1a\u79d1\u5b66\u51fa\u7248\u793e|location=Beijing|isbn=978-7-5004-0432-3}}\n* {{citation |last=Yu |first=Pauline |title=Charting the Landscape of Chinese Poetry |journal=Chinese Literature: Essays, Articles, Reviews (CLEAR) |year=1998|volume=20 |pages=71\u201387 |jstor=495264 |doi=10.2307/495264 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Yule |first=Henry |authorlink=Henry Yule |year=1915 |orig-year=1866 |editor-last=Cordier |editor-first=Henri |title=Cathay and the Way Thither: Being a Collection of Medieval Notices of China |url = https://archive.org/stream/cathaywaythither01yule |location=London |publisher=[[Hakluyt Society]] |volume=1 |edition=New |ref=harv }}\n{{refend}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{citation |last=Abramson|first=Marc S.|title=Ethnic Identity in Tang China|year=2008|publisher=University of Pennsylvania Press|location=Philadelphia|isbn=978-0-8122-4052-8|ref=none}}\n* {{citation |last=Barrett |first=Timothy Hugh |title=The Woman Who Discovered Printing |year=2008 |publisher=[[Yale University Press]]|location=Great Britain |isbn=978-0-300-12728-7 |ref=none}}\n* {{citation|last=Cotterell|first=Arthur|title=The Imperial Capitals of China: An Inside 