iversitaria, Universidad de Puerto Rico,1969}}</ref><ref name=\"Law2015\">{{cite book|author=Gwillim Law|title=Administrative Subdivisions of Countries: A Comprehensive World Reference, 1900 through 1998| url =https://books.google.com/books?id=nXCeCQAAQBAJ|accessdate=25 December 2018|date=20 May 2015|publisher=McFarland|isbn=978-1-4766-0447-3|page=300}}</ref><ref name= \"2010 Census\">{{cite book|title=Puerto Rico:2010:population and housing unit counts.pdf | url = https://permanent.access.gpo.gov/gpo35934/cph-2-53.pdf|year=2010|publisher=U.S. Dept. of Commerce, Economics and Statistics Administration, U.S. Census Bureau}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nWhen after the [[Treaty of Paris (1898)]], the U.S. conducted its first census of Puerto Rico, the population of Yaurel barrio was 1,333.<ref name=\"OfficeSanger1900\">{{cite book|author1=Joseph Prentiss Sanger|author2=Henry Gannett|author3=Walter Francis Willcox|title=Informe sobre el censo de Puerto Rico, 1899, United States. War Dept. Porto Rico Census Office|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cZ9QAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA162|year=1900|publisher=Imprenta del gobierno|page=162| language=es}}</ref>\n\n==Special community==\nSince 2001 when law 1-2001 was passed,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lexjuris.com/lexlex/Leyes2001/lex2001001.htm|title=Leyes del 2001|website=Lex Juris Puerto Rico|language=es|accessdate=24 June 2019}}</ref> measures have been taken to identify and address the high levels of poverty and the lack of resources and opportunities affecting specific communities in Puerto Rico. Initially there were 686 places that made the list.<ref name=\"wordpress.com\">{{cite web|url=https://cpprbib.wordpress.com/biblioteca-virtual/guias-tematicas/comunidades-especiales/comunidades-especiales-de-puerto-rico/|title=Comunidades Especiales de Puerto Rico|date=8 August 2011|language=es|accessdate=24 June 2019}}</ref> By 2008, there were 742 places on the list of {{lang|es|Comunidades especiales de Puerto Rico}}. The places on the list are barrios, communities, sectors, or neighborhoods and in 2004, Yaurel barrio made the list.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elnuevodia.com/noticias/locales/nota/evolucionaelproyectodecomunidadesespeciales-2294682/|title=Evoluciona el proyecto de Comunidades Especiales|date=24 February 2017|newspaper=El Nuevo Dia|language=es|accessdate=24 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elvocero.com/gobierno/ya-es-ley-oficina-para-el-desarrollo-socioecon-mico-y/article_54769072-382d-5156-9acf-9e8c0b4f4d82.html|title=Ya es ley Oficina para el Desarrollo Socioecon\u00f3mico y Comunitario|first=Por|last=ElVocero.com|newspaper=El Vocero de Puerto Rico|language=es|accessdate=24 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of communities in Puerto Rico]]\n\n==References==\n{{Portal|Puerto Rico}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Barrios of Arroyo, Puerto Rico]]\n\n\n{{PuertoRico-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "The Eloquent Peasant", "label": "safe", "comment": "reworded history paragraph, replaced: When after \u2192 The United", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yaurel,_Arroyo,_Puerto_Rico"}
{"title_page": "The Daily (podcast)", "text_new": "{{short description|News podcast by The New York Times}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox podcast\n| title = The Daily\n| image = The_Daily_logo.jpg\n| image_size = 200px\n| hosting = [[Michael Barbaro]]\n| genre = [[Long-form journalism]]\n| language = English\n| updates = Weekdays\n| length = avg. 20\u201325 minutes\n| direction = <!-- For direction credits -->\n| production = {{Collapsible list\n  |framestyle=border:none; padding:0; <!--Hides borders and improves row spacing-->\n  |title=Producers\n|Theo Balcomb |Andy Mills |Lisa Tobin |Rachel Quester |Lynsea Garrison |Annie Brown |Clare Toeniskoetter |Paige Cowett |Michael Simon Johnson |Brad Fisher |Larissa Anderson |Wendy Dorr |Chris Wood |Jessica Cheung |Alexandra Leigh Young |Jonathan Wolfe |Lisa Chow |Eric Krupke |Marc Georges |Luke Vander Ploeg |Adizah Eghan\n}}\n| theme_music_composer = Jim Brunberg and Ben Landsverk\n| num_seasons = \n| num_episodes = <!-- actual number of episodes, if known -->\n| list_episodes = <!-- Wikipedia \"List of\" article (( don't include [[ ]]).-->\n| began = {{start_date|2017|2|1}}\n| ended = <!-- or 'final'; date of last airing (if applicable) -->\n| ratings = \n| cited_for = <!-- Any awards, -->\n| cited_as = <!-- honors, recognitions, etc. -->\n| provider = ''[[The New York Times]]''\n| related_shows = \n| website = {{URL|https://www.nytimes.com/column/the-daily|NYTimes.com/column/the-daily}}\n}}\n\n'''''The Daily''''' is a daily news [[podcast]] and radio show by the American newspaper ''[[The New York Times]]''. Hosted by ''Times'' political journalist [[Michael Barbaro]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pbs.org/newshour/brief/246115/michael-barbaro|title=Michael Barbaro, Journalist|website=Brief but Spectacular|language=en-US|access-date=November 25, 2019}}</ref> its episodes are based on the ''Times''{{'}} reporting of the day with interviews of journalists from the New York Times. Episodes last 20 to 30 minutes, and new episodes air every weekday.\n\nThe Daily launched in January of 2017 as an extension of The New York Times' 2016 election-focused podcast, ''The Run-Up''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nymag.com/intelligencer/2020/01/michael-barbaro-the-daily-podcast-new-york-times.html|title=The Voice of the Podcast Generation|last=Schneier|first=Matthew|date=2020-01-21|website=Intelligencer|language=en-us|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref>\n\n''The Daily'' is based on interviews with ''Times'' journalists,<ref name=\"The New Yorker 21 August 2017\">{{cite news|last1=Mead|first1=Rebecca|title=An Appreciation of Michael Barbaro and \u201cThe Daily\u201d|url=https://www.newyorker.com/culture/cultural-comment/an-appreciation-of-michael-barbaro-and-the-daily|accessdate=November 19, 2017|work=The New Yorker|date=August 21, 2017}}</ref> in which they summarize and comment on their story, and is complemented by recordings related to the topic, or original reporting such as interviews with persons involved in the story. A summary of headlines concludes the podcast.\n\n''The Daily'' is free to listen and financed by advertising; it is profitable according to the ''Times''.<ref>{{Cite web| last = Siegel| first = Tatiana| title = Michael Barbaro and 'The Daily' Podcast Team on Launching 'The Weekly' FX Series, Working With a Romantic Partner| work = Hollywood Reporter| accessdate = June 16, 2019| url = https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/michael-barbaro-daily-podcast-team-launching-weekly-fx-series-1200451}}</ref> The ''Times'' said it intended to build a news podcast franchise around it, beginning with a spin-off podcast, ''The New Washington'', in summer 2017.<ref name=\"TheStreet 17 October 2017\" /> ''The New Washington'' ran from July 2017 until December of the same year.<ref>{{citation |last=Grinapol |first=Corinne | title=The New York Times Unveils Another Politics Podcast, Called The New Washington |url=https://www.adweek.com/digital/the-new-york-times-unveils-another-politics-podcast-called-the-new-washington/ |accessdate=January 16, 2019}}</ref> A children's edition of ''The Daily'' was also planned.<ref>{{cite news|title=A regular New York Times kids\u2019 section and a kids\u2019 version of The Daily are on the way this month|url=http://www.niemanlab.org/2017/11/a-new-york-times-kids-section-once-an-experiment-will-run-monthly-starting-this-month/|accessdate=November 19, 2017|work=Nieman Lab}}</ref> In January 2019, ''The Daily'' launched a weekly newsletter.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/01/14/podcasts/subscribe-daily-podcast-newsletter.html|title=Subscribe to a Newsletter From \u2018The Daily\u2019|date=January 14, 2019|work=The New York Times|access-date=June 16, 2019|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== ''The Weekly'' (spinoff) ==\nThe success of the podcast led to a weekly documentary series called ''[[The Weekly]]'', which was announced on May 8, 2019 by FX and debuted on June 2, 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/09/business/media/new-york-times-daily-podcast-tv.html|title=With \u2018The Weekly,\u2019 The New York Times Gets Serious About TV|last=Koblin|first=John|date=May 9, 2018|work=The New York Times|access-date=June 2, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> The Weekly is an American narrative investigative journalism docuseries that covers recent topical news and cultural stories.\n\n== Reception ==\nStarted in January 2017, ''The Daily'' became a noted success for the ''Times'';  ''[[TheStreet.com]]'' described it as \"a phenomenon, an out-of-the-blue hit\".<ref name=\"TheStreet 17 October 2017\">{{cite news|last1=Doctor|first1=Ken|title=New York Times' breakthrough 'The Daily' soars past 100M download mark|url=https://www.thestreet.com/story/14344163/1/times-breakthrough-the-daily-soars-past-the-100-million-download-mark.html|accessdate=November 19, 2017|work=TheStreet|date=October 17, 2017}}</ref> It had 3.8 million individual listeners by August 2017,<ref>{{cite web|title=\u201cThe Daily\u201d Exceeds 100 Million Downloads|url=https://www.nytco.com/the-daily-exceeds-100-million-downloads/|publisher=The New York Times Company|accessdate=November 19, 2017|date=October 17, 2017}}</ref> and was regularly in the top ten most-listened podcasts by autumn 2017.<ref name=\"TheStreet 17 October 2017\" /> ''[[The New Yorker]]'' attributed this success, in part, to the podcast's \"conversational and intimate\" tone, which made news more accessible, and to Barbaro's \"idiosyncratic intonation\" (he is known to have a very distinct \"hm\" after commentary from guest journalists).<ref name=\"The New Yorker 21 August 2017\" /> The podcast began being syndicated to radio by [[American Public Media]] in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web| last = Falk| first = Tyler| title = New York Times\u2019 \u2018The Daily\u2019 podcast headed to public radio| work = Current| accessdate = April 28, 2018| url = https://current.org/2018/02/new-york-times-the-daily-podcast-headed-to-public-radio/}}</ref> As of June 2018, the podcast receives 1.1 million downloads every weekday<ref>{{Cite web| last = Johnson| first = Eric| title = Michael Barbaro explains why The Daily podcast doesn\u2019t cover Donald Trump\u2019s tweets| work = Recode| accessdate = June 16, 2019| url = https://www.vox.com/2018/6/18/17473856/michael-barbaro-new-york-times-daily-podcast-kara-swisher-recode-decode-live-interview-trump-tweets}}</ref> and 2 millions in January 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://podmust.com/what-makes-the-daily-so-unique/|title=What makes The Daily so unique? \u2022 PodMust|date=2020-01-26|website=PodMust|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-10}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of daily news podcasts]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official|https://www.nytimes.com/column/the-daily}}\n*[https://www.nytimes.com/podcasts/the-daily Most recent episode]\n*[https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/the-daily/id1200361736 The Daily on Apple Podcasts]\n*[https://www.podchaser.com/podcasts/the-daily-243479 The Daily on Podchaser]\n\n{{NY Times}}\n{{American Public Media}}\n\n[[Category:2017 podcast debuts]]\n[[Category:Political podcasts]]\n[[Category:The New York Times]]\n[[Category:Audio podcasts]]\n[[Category:Talk podcasts]]\n[[Category:American journalism]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|News podcast by The New York Times}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox podcast\n| title = The Daily\n| image = The_Daily_logo.jpg\n| image_size = 200px\n| hosting = [[Michael Barbaro]]\n| genre = [[Long-form journalism]]\n| language = English\n| updates = Weekdays\n| length = avg. 20\u201325 minutes\n| direction = <!-- For direction credits -->\n| production = {{Collapsible list\n  |framestyle=border:none; padding:0; <!--Hides borders and improves row spacing-->\n  |title=Producers\n|Theo Balcomb |Andy Mills |Lisa Tobin |Rachel Quester |Lynsea Garrison |Annie Brown |Clare Toeniskoetter |Paige Cowett |Michael Simon Johnson |Brad Fisher |Larissa Anderson |Wendy Dorr |Chris Wood |Jessica Cheung |Alexandra Leigh Young |Jonathan Wolfe |Lisa Chow |Eric Krupke |Marc Georges |Luke Vander Ploeg |Adizah Eghan\n}}\n| theme_music_composer = Jim Brunberg and Ben Landsverk\n| num_seasons = \n| num_episodes = <!-- actual number of episodes, if known -->\n| list_episodes = <!-- Wikipedia \"List of\" article (( don't include [[ ]]).-->\n| began = {{start_date|2017|2|1}}\n| ended = <!-- or 'final'; date of last airing (if applicable) -->\n| ratings = \n| cited_for = <!-- Any awards, -->\n| cited_as = <!-- honors, recognitions, etc. -->\n| provider = ''[[The New York Times]]''\n| related_shows = \n| website = {{URL|https://www.nytimes.com/column/the-daily|NYTimes.com/column/the-daily}}\n}}\n\n'''''The Daily''''' is a daily news [[podcast]] and radio show by the American newspaper ''[[The New York Times]]''. Hosted by ''Times'' political journalist [[Michael Barbaro]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pbs.org/newshour/brief/246115/michael-barbaro|title=Michael Barbaro, Journalist|website=Brief but Spectacular|language=en-US|access-date=November 25, 2019}}</ref> its episodes are based on the ''Times''{{'}} reporting of the day with interviews of journalists from the New York Times. Episodes last 20 to 30 minutes, and new episodes air every weekday.\n\nThe Daily launched in January of 2017 as an extension of The New York Times' 2016 election-focused podcast, ''The Run-Up''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nymag.com/intelligencer/2020/01/michael-barbaro-the-daily-podcast-new-york-times.html|title=The Voice of the Podcast Generation|last=Schneier|first=Matthew|date=2020-01-21|website=Intelligencer|language=en-us|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref>\n\n''The Daily'' is based on interviews with ''Times'' journalists,<ref name=\"The New Yorker 21 August 2017\">{{cite news|last1=Mead|first1=Rebecca|title=An Appreciation of Michael Barbaro and \u201cThe Daily\u201d|url=https://www.newyorker.com/culture/cultural-comment/an-appreciation-of-michael-barbaro-and-the-daily|accessdate=November 19, 2017|work=The New Yorker|date=August 21, 2017}}</ref> in which they summarize and comment on their story, and is complemented by recordings related to the topic, or original reporting such as interviews with persons involved in the story. A summary of headlines concludes the podcast.\n\n''The Daily'' is free to listen and financed by advertising; it is profitable according to the ''Times''.<ref>{{Cite web| last = Siegel| first = Tatiana| title = Michael Barbaro and 'The Daily' Podcast Team on Launching 'The Weekly' FX Series, Working With a Romantic Partner| work = Hollywood Reporter| accessdate = June 16, 2019| url = https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/michael-barbaro-daily-podcast-team-launching-weekly-fx-series-1200451}}</ref> The ''Times'' has said it intends to build a news podcast franchise around it, beginning with a spin-off podcast, ''The New Washington'', in summer 2017.<ref name=\"TheStreet 17 October 2017\" /> ''The New Washington'' ran from July 2017 until December of the same year.<ref>{{citation |last=Grinapol |first=Corinne | title=The New York Times Unveils Another Politics Podcast, Called The New Washington |url=https://www.adweek.com/digital/the-new-york-times-unveils-another-politics-podcast-called-the-new-washington/ |accessdate=January 16, 2019}}</ref> A children's edition of ''The Daily'' is also planned.<ref>{{cite news|title=A regular New York Times kids\u2019 section and a kids\u2019 version of The Daily are on the way this month|url=http://www.niemanlab.org/2017/11/a-new-york-times-kids-section-once-an-experiment-will-run-monthly-starting-this-month/|accessdate=November 19, 2017|work=Nieman Lab}}</ref> In January 2019, ''The Daily'' launched a weekly newsletter.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/01/14/podcasts/subscribe-daily-podcast-newsletter.html|title=Subscribe to a Newsletter From \u2018The Daily\u2019|date=January 14, 2019|work=The New York Times|access-date=June 16, 2019|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== ''The Weekly'' (spinoff) ==\nThe success of the podcast led to a weekly documentary series called ''[[The Weekly]]'', which was announced on May 8, 2019 by FX and debuted on June 2, 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/09/business/media/new-york-times-daily-podcast-tv.html|title=With \u2018The Weekly,\u2019 The New York Times Gets Serious About TV|last=Koblin|first=John|date=May 9, 2018|work=The New York Times|access-date=June 2, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> The Weekly is an American narrative investigative journalism docuseries that covers recent topical news and cultural stories.\n\n== Reception ==\nStarted in January 2017, ''The Daily'' became a noted success for the ''Times'';  ''[[TheStreet.com]]'' described it as \"a phenomenon, an out-of-the-blue hit\".<ref name=\"TheStreet 17 October 2017\">{{cite news|last1=Doctor|first1=Ken|title=New York Times' breakthrough 'The Daily' soars past 100M download mark|url=https://www.thestreet.com/story/14344163/1/times-breakthrough-the-daily-soars-past-the-100-million-download-mark.html|accessdate=November 19, 2017|work=TheStreet|date=October 17, 2017}}</ref> It had 3.8 million individual listeners by August 2017,<ref>{{cite web|title=\u201cThe Daily\u201d Exceeds 100 Million Downloads|url=https://www.nytco.com/the-daily-exceeds-100-million-downloads/|publisher=The New York Times Company|accessdate=November 19, 2017|date=October 17, 2017}}</ref> and was regularly in the top ten most-listened podcasts by autumn 2017.<ref name=\"TheStreet 17 October 2017\" /> ''[[The New Yorker]]'' attributed this success, in part, to the podcast's \"conversational and intimate\" tone, which made news more accessible, and to Barbaro's \"idiosyncratic intonation\" (he is known to have a very distinct \"hm\" after commentary from guest journalists).<ref name=\"The New Yorker 21 August 2017\" /> The podcast began being syndicated to radio by [[American Public Media]] in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web| last = Falk| first = Tyler| title = New York Times\u2019 \u2018The Daily\u2019 podcast headed to public radio| work = Current| accessdate = April 28, 2018| url = https://current.org/2018/02/new-york-times-the-daily-podcast-headed-to-public-radio/}}</ref> As of June 2018, the podcast receives 1.1 million downloads every weekday<ref>{{Cite web| last = Johnson| first = Eric| title = Michael Barbaro explains why The Daily podcast doesn\u2019t cover Donald Trump\u2019s tweets| work = Recode| accessdate = June 16, 2019| url = https://www.vox.com/2018/6/18/17473856/michael-barbaro-new-york-times-daily-podcast-kara-swisher-recode-decode-live-interview-trump-tweets}}</ref> and 2 millions in January 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://podmust.com/what-makes-the-daily-so-unique/|title=What makes The Daily so unique? \u2022 PodMust|date=2020-01-26|website=PodMust|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-10}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of daily news podcasts]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n